# Published-package excludes — fallback safety net (release prep).
#
# PRIMARY mechanism: package.json "files" is a tight allowlist that names only
# the runtime pieces of ui/ (ui/**/*.py, ui/*.md, ui/web/dist/). Because the
# frontend build tree is never selected by that allowlist, the dev toolchain and
# its node_modules cannot ship. NOTE (npm precedence): a root .npmignore CANNOT
# subtract from a directory that "files" lists explicitly — so this file does not
# override "files"; it only bites paths npm would otherwise include by default.
#
# This file is therefore the SECOND layer: if "files" is ever loosened back to a
# whole-directory entry (e.g. "ui/") or removed entirely, these rules still keep
# the dev-only frontend build toolchain and its dependencies out of the tarball.
# The published package ships the RUNTIME dashboard (the committed Vite build at
# ui/web/dist plus the ui/*.py server that serves it) — never the build toolchain.

# Frontend build toolchain & dependencies (dev-only).
# ui/web/dist is intentionally NOT listed here, so it always ships.
ui/web/node_modules/
ui/web/src/
ui/web/index.html
ui/web/package.json
ui/web/package-lock.json
ui/web/tsconfig.json
ui/web/tsconfig.*.json
ui/web/vite.config.ts
ui/web/vitest.config.ts
ui/web/*.config.ts
ui/web/*.config.js
ui/web/.gitattributes

# Developer documentation (CLAUDE.md files) — internal only, never ship.
tools/CLAUDE.md
ui/CLAUDE.md
state_store/CLAUDE.md
CLAUDE-TEMPLATE.md

# Archived/deprecated documentation (personal paths, sensitive content).
docs/archive/

# Python compiled artifacts & cache (dev-only, never ship).
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.pytest_cache/
